      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUGATTI RICO (4) was always well back but did hit the line strongly late to finish 4th and beaten only 5 lengths (18.63) at Richmond. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Has ability and can bounce back. REALLY SAVAGE (8) is not generally a safe beginner. Latest effort finished 4th over 340m at this track beaten 7 lengths (19.84) behind Battle Speed in a Grade 5 on June 2. Looks one of the chances. CASH WORTH (2) was a winner two back when prominent throughout then got further back last time and could manage only a 14 length 8th at Richmond (23.69). Likely to be about the mark. MIGHTY SEVEN (1) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
